title: For Sale:  FOR SALE: SMITH & WESSON MODEL 66 POLICE ISSUE
postcontent:
S&W Model 66 ... K-frame ... stainless steel ... 357 Mag caliber ... 6" barrel ... 12 1/2" overall ... weight 38.5 oz ... serrated target trigger ... checkered target hammer ... adjustable square notch rear sight & red ramp front sight ... Goncalo Alves checkered grips ... trigger pull of 4 pounds 4 oz.

This is number 16 of a 200 gun production run made specially for the Rhode Island State Police in the early 1970's. After receiving the firearms, the troopers determined that they prefered the 4" barrel. They returned 198 of the guns to the distributor. (The govenor kept #1 and his driver kept #2.) Smith & Wesson made them 200 new model 66's with the 4" barrel but refused to put the lanyard swivel. The distributor sold the remaining 198 original guns in the late 1970's. This is the only stainless steel gun that S&W ever made with a lanyard swivel.

This near perfect firearm comes in the original metal cornered box with the owner's manual, parts list, all paperwork and the S&W cleaning kit.

title: For Sale/Trade:  1919 8mm Lebel Berthier Carbine
postcontent:
This is a great looking French Army Rifle.  It is has a five round capacity but does not include a 5round en bloc clip.  I have fired the rifle and everything works great accept that the clip ejector releases but does not forcibly eject the spent clip.  As to the condition of the rifle I would say that it is clearly a used military rifle and thus has repairs to the stock and non-matching numbers from being taken apart and cleaned.  All around it is a great piece of history and would look great hanging in a man cave, trophy room or out at the range.

I also have around 500 rounds of military ammunition.  Keep in mind that the ammunition is also very old and so there will likely be misfires and hang fires........The price we pay as die-hard collectors!  The ammunition is on 24 round stripper clips used on the Hotchkiss machine gun, however,  can be popped off for shooting in this rifle.

I am asking 60 cents per round ($60 per 100) for the ammunition though I will make a deal if you buy the rifle or a large amount of ammo.

Thanks for looking and let me know if you have questions or want more pictures.

Cash or Trade only, must be at least 21 to purchase.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Duotone Sig P226R - W German, rail, night sights, 7 hi-caps, NP3 ROBAR coating
postcontent:
This was my holy grail gun for a long time. It has many unique features beyond a traditional 226

#1: This is a railed, German-made pistol - the proof marks and prized triple serial numbers are present. German-made versions with a rail are exceptionally rare - railed variants are typically only the lower-quality American versions.

#2: The slide, controls, and internals have been sent out to ROBAR for their NP3 treatment. For those of you unfamiliar with it, it's essentially a chrome/teflon coating that makes it impervious to rust/weather. It's amazing - I find that cleaning only needs to consist of wiping a cotton cloth across it, the residue falls off.

Comes with:

Original hard case
Bright Sig night sights
Six 18 round mags
One 20 round mag

*Note - these mags will be illegal to purchase after July 1st, and there will be no more private sales of guns after that either*

I'm not in a hurry to get rid of this. It's smooth as silk in it's functionality, and deadly accurate out to 25 yards. I just have come to the conclusion that it's going to be too large for practical carry for me (I'm skinny), and I will probably always be a die-hard Glock fan.

title: Want To Buy:  RG Revolvers, .38 Spl. & .44 Mag
postcontent: I'm looking for RG revolvers. I worked in the gun business many years ago and we had a showcase full of them. When someone wanted a gun to put in the drawer and probably never fire it we steered them over to the "Bargain Basement" and sold them an RG. Those guns always made me laugh with their thin blueing (?) and shiny plastic grips. Some of them you would pull out the cylinder pin, remove the cylinder and use the pin to poke out the empties. Brilliant designs, I fired one once and it spat back at me and pierced my earlobe with a sliver of lead. They actually made a .44 Mag but I was afraid to fire it. I'm feeling nostalgic and figure there has to be some of those old RG's out there I can play with. I'm looking for servicable ones (as servicable as can be) and I'll pay a fair price or trade. What have you got?. Thanks, John

Designed specifically for military-issue MK11/M110 rifles and mil-spec ammunition (including M118LR), the PMAG 20LR is less than half the weight of standard issue steel magazines and maintains a service life round count approximately equal to the rifle barrel itself.

When the PMAG 20LR is inserted into the magazine well, some MWS rifles exhibit interference between the bolt catch and the rear of the magazine. This can cause partial engagement of the bolt catch and result in unintentional contact between the bolt carrier group and the bolt catch during normal weapon operation. This gun holds 5+1 rounds
